Citizens who are over 60 and have registered to receive the vaccine on the government's system will soon receive a message to schedule their appointments as the Minister of Health Zweli Mkhize said they were still on track to start the next phase of vaccinations. Spokesperson Lwazi Manzi added that the first Pfizer vaccines will be administered after May 15, 2021 and that the department was still waiting for an audit of the Johnson & Johnson vaccines to be concluded at the Aspen Pharmacare site.           As of May 12, 2021, over 1,599,272 cases of Covid-19 have been confirmed of which 54,896 proved fatal and 1,519,258 resulted in recovery while 395,230 vaccinations have been administered.